An 80-year-old woman has died after the car she was travelling in crashed outside a pub.The blue Volkswagen Polo crashed outside The Hawk Inn in Amport, near Andover, Hampshire, at about 15:20 BST on Thursday. The Polo's driver, an 81-year-old woman from Somerset, was arrested on suspicion of causing death by careless driving. She was released on bail until 4 July.  
